{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a1789abc-9015-4a5f-9013-fded18ca5cdd","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why?**\n\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, inner exception, etc.)\n- The test fails properly if no exception is thrown","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cab92e9f-8439-4ff4-ac9e-bdff9ea775d9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":239,"requestId":"042C:25FEDD:1847BDC:1BAAFCF:69E820FF"},"id":"30aaf200-6af3-470e-910c-cb8cbe59b00c","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:14:46.247Z","parentId":"5c233b80-d84b-485d-a239-5e73e05ae433"}
